properties.Name: InsurancePolicyBeneficiary
properties.Description:
An individual person(s) or legal entity(s) who may be eligible to receive or is receiving benefits under an insurance policy other than the participant.

There are potentially two types of beneficiary (INDIVIDUAL and LEGAL ENTITY), where a Legal Entity is an artificial legal creation such as a corporation, sole proprietorship, partnership.

There are several types of beneficiary relationships that may exist:

- Irrevocable beneficiary
- Revocable beneficiary
- Primary beneficiary
- Secondary beneficiary
- Tertiary beneficiary
- Contingent beneficiary

Columns.Name: InsurancePolicyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Policy.

Columns.Name: BeneficiaryId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Beneficiary.

Columns.Name: DateNamedBeneficiary
Columns.Description: The date that the beneficiary was named to the insurance policy.

Columns.Name: DateRemovedAsBeneficiary
Columns.Description: The date that the beneficiary was removed as beneficiary of the Insurance Policy.

Columns.Name: ProceedsPercentage
Columns.Description: The percentage split amongst the respective beneficiaries named in the insurance policy.

Columns.Name: ProceedsAmount
Columns.Description: The dollar amount split amongst the respective beneficiaries named in the insurance policy.

Columns.Name: DistributionPerStirpesIndicator
Columns.Description: The policy proceeds are paid only to the beneficiaries wo are living and have been named in the policy.

Columns.Name: DistributionPerCapitaIndicator
Columns.Description:
The distribution is claimed on the behalf of the Beneficiary.

This is in contrast to the per stirpes beneficiary who receives the proceeds through the rights of another.

Columns.Name: PolicyholderBeneficiaryRelationshipTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Policyholder Beneficiary Relationship Type.

Columns.Name: RelationshipToInsured
Columns.Description: The relationship of the Beneficiary to the insured.

Columns.Name: InsurableInterestTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Insurable Interest Type.

Columns.Name: RevocableBeneficiaryIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the Beneficiary designation is or is not revocable.

Columns.Name: FacilityOfPaymentInEffectIndicator
Columns.Description: A clause permitted under a uniform health insurance policy provision that allows companies to pay up to $1,000of benefits or proceeds to any relative appearing entitled to it if there is no beneficiary or if the insured or beneficiary is a minor or legally incompetent.

Columns.Name: ReasonForBeneficiaryChange
Columns.Description: The reason that the beneficiary was changed.

Columns.Name: DistributionMethodId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Distribution Method.

Columns.Name: OrderOfSuccessionId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a specific Succession Order.

Columns.Name: BeneficiaryRevocationStatusId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Beneficiary Revocation Status.

Properties.Description:
An individual person(s) or legal entity(s) who may be eligible to receive or is receiving benefits under an insurance policy other than the participant.

There are potentially two types of beneficiary (INDIVIDUAL and LEGAL ENTITY), where a Legal Entity is an artificial legal creation such as a corporation, sole proprietorship, partnership.

There are several types of beneficiary relationships that may exist:

- Irrevocable beneficiary
- Revocable beneficiary
- Primary beneficiary
- Secondary beneficiary
- Tertiary beneficiary
- Contingent beneficiary
